 of white authorities. In this first extended study of the social significance of Powell’s place in the American musical landscape, Guthrie P. Ramsey, Jr. shows how the pianist expanded his own artistic horizons and moved his chosen idiom into new realms. Illuminating and multi-layered, The Amazing Bud Powell centralizes Powell’s contributions as it details the collision of two vibrant political economies: the discourses of art and the practice of blackness.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Jazz.2bisacsh  a20th century.  aafrican american biographies.  aafrican american studies.  aalcohol abuse.  aamerican music.  aart.  aartistic horizons.  aartists.  abebop idiom.  abebop.  abiography.  ablack biographies.  aentertainment industry.  aexceptional talent.  aexpansive musicianship.  ahistory of jazz music.  ahistory.  ainventive compositions.  ajazz music.  ajazz musicians biographies.  amental health issues.  amisunderstood figures.  amusic.  amusical genres.  amusical minds.  amusicians.  apianist.  ariveting performances.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052024391040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095515840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520955158423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520955158/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY